item.description:
With the release of Swift 2.2 in Xcode 7.3 C-style for loops have become deprecated. The default Xcode fix-it for converting them uses a Range:
let count = 5 for var index = 0; index &lt; count; index++ { doSomething(index) } is converted do:
let count = 5 for index in 0 ..&lt; count { doSomething(index) } For the vast majority of C-style for loops this will work perfectly well. But there are cases where using a Range not only won&rsquo;t work as expected but will actually crash!
